This is a Learning Machine Learning Algorithm Notebook¶

There are multiple Algorithms, and with each algorithm, we have a following procedure of example

  • Extracting or collecting dataset
  • Spliting it for traning and testing
  • Train the Model
  • Test the Model
  • Finding the accuracy or matrics
  • Plotting the graphs

Linear Regression¶

Predict future by past experiences linearly changing¶

Example: We are using numpy arrays: pandas : datasets, matplotlib: ploting lib, sklearn: lot more function for ML

Preparing the data¶

In [35]:
X = data[['Avg. Area Income', 'Avg. Area House Age', 'Avg. Area Number of Rooms',
       'Avg. Area Number of Bedrooms', 'Area Population']]
Y = data[['Price']]
train_x, test_x , train_y, test_y = train_test_split(X,Y,test_size=0.2,random_state=0)

Now Train the model¶

In [44]:
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(train_x,train_y)
print(f'Model slope: {model.coef_}')
print(f'Model Intercept: {model.intercept_}')

Model slope: [[2.16604083e+01 1.65809651e+05 1.20329408e+05 2.19309558e+03
  1.52858855e+01]]
Model Intercept: [-2646630.53105591]

Testing the model using TestDataSet¶

In [34]:
result = model.predict(test_x)

Calculating accuracy¶

In [42]:
# Finding the absolute mean error
mean_error = mean_absolute_error(result,test_y)
mean_error
r2 = r2_score(result,test_y)
r2
accuracy = pd.DataFrame([{'Absolute mean Error': mean_error , "r2 Score": r2}])

accuracy
